<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
    <id>4332</id>
    <title>Nothing happens when offline and tapping the SEND button in user Invite screen</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">### Expected behavior</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.2">In the user Invite Screen, tapping "SEND" while typing a username should bring up some form of error message to denote the inability to perform the action while offline</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">### Actual behavior</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">Tapping SEND in those conditions only buttonizes the username and then nothing happens.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">### Steps to reproduce the behavior</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.2">- Go into the user Invites screen by visiting MySite &gt; People and tapping the "+" button on the actionbar</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.3">- Put the device to offline mode</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.4">- Start typing a username and before hitting "enter"</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.5">- Tap the "SEND" action</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.6">- The username mutates into a "button" like widget</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.7">- Nothing else happens.</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.8">##### Tested on [device], Android [version]</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Nexus 5X emulator running Android 6.0</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
